    },
    {
      "title": "The 'Emergent Generalization' Hand-Wave",
      "description": "The claim of 'emergent generalization' is largely an assertion of hope rather than a concrete design. Simply exchanging models among specialized agents does not guarantee that higher-level, coherent, and robust generalization will spontaneously appear, especially across vastly different domains. This is a leap of faith, not a detailed architectural component, and often masks a lack of understanding of how such complex emergent behaviors would be reliably engineered."
